VODs Project Documentation
Overview
VODs is a React application built with TypeScript and Vite, providing a modern development experience with fast refresh and type safety.

Technology Stack

React - UI library for building user interfaces
TypeScript - Typed superset of JavaScript
Vite - Fast build tool and dev server with HMR
ESLint - Code quality and style linter
npm - Package manager

Project Structure

VODs/
├── src/              # Application source code
├── public/           # Static assets
├── node_modules/     # Dependencies
├── package.json      # npm configuration
├── tsconfig.json     # TypeScript configuration
├── vite.config.ts    # Vite configuration
└── eslint.config.js  # ESLint configuration

Installation & Running

Install Dependencies
npm install

Development Mode
npm run dev

Production Build
npm run build

Preview Production Build
npm run preview

Configuration Features

Hot Module Replacement (HMR)

The project uses HMR for instant updates without page reload during development.

Vite Plugins

Two official plugins are available:

@vitejs/plugin-react - uses Babel for Fast Refresh
@vitejs/plugin-react-swc - uses SWC for faster Fast Refresh

Development Guidelines

ESLint Configuration

For production applications, consider:

Enabling type-aware TypeScript rules
Configuring parserOptions with tsconfig paths
Using strict presets like plugin:@typescript-eslint/recommended-type-checked
Adding eslint-plugin-react for React-specific rules

Component Structure

Place components in src/components/
Use TypeScript for all files (.tsx, .ts)
Follow functional components pattern with hooks
Adhere to ESLint rules

